body:
Hello. I want to implement a circular buffer and process data based on several previous signals. So i have a buffer and wires to previous signals declared like that:
```
wire [63:0] prev_value1;
wire [63:0] prev_value2;

assign prev_value1 = buffer[index - 1];
assign prev_value2 = buffer[index - 2];
etc...
```
When i test this code on my icoBoard with Lattice iCE HX8K FPGA, the indices work as i expected. I always get correct previous value in the buffer. But when i simulate it using iVerilog, on underflow the values are X. It seems like the index overflow is going wrong. When i create additional registers with desired bit size everything works as i expect. I think index should be trimmed on underflow to have the same size as the buffer and show correct value without additional register.

GTKWave output:

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/10122409/48054142-9c2c0800-e1bd-11e8-875d-5a4664e28e04.png)

Code to reproduce the issue:

```


module test_module(input clk,
				   input rst);

   reg [2:0] 	 index = 0;

   reg [8:0]		 buffer = 8'b10101010;

   wire 			 prev_value1;
   wire 			 prev_value2;
   wire 			 prev_value3;
   wire 			 prev_value4;

   //shows wrong value
   assign prev_value1 = buffer[index - 1];
   assign prev_value2 = buffer[index - 2];
   assign prev_value3 = buffer[index - 3];
   assign prev_value4 = buffer[index - 4];

   
   wire [2:0] 		 index1;
   wire [2:0] 		 index2;
   wire [2:0] 		 index3;
   wire [2:0] 		 index4;

   //assigning indices to 3 bit registers
   assign index1 = index - 1;
   assign index2 = index - 2;
   assign index3 = index - 3;
   assign index4 = index - 4;

   
   wire 			 real_prev_value1;
   wire 			 real_prev_value2;
   wire 			 real_prev_value3;
   wire 			 real_prev_value4;

   //shows real value
   assign real_prev_value1 = buffer[index1];
   assign real_prev_value2 = buffer[index2];
   assign real_prev_value3 = buffer[index3];
   assign real_prev_value4 = buffer[index4];

   always @(posedge clk) begin
	  index = index + 1;
   end

endmodule

```

